1
00:01:32,039 --> 00:01:34,950
[How dare you!?]

2
00:01:35,009 --> 00:01:40,020
[Episode 20]

3
00:01:48,789 --> 00:01:50,050
There's still someone

4
00:01:52,280 --> 00:01:53,810
waiting for me to come back.

5
00:02:22,670 --> 00:02:23,670
♪ Tell me ♪

6
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:27,829
♪ Why so many laments echo in the wind ♪

7
00:02:29,390 --> 00:02:30,540
♪ Walk past me ♪

8
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:34,670
♪ Like an aloof passerby ♪

9
00:02:35,930 --> 00:02:38,460
♪ Don't watch me as the rain falls ♪

10
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:42,020
♪ Love burns too hot as it passes ♪

11
00:02:42,829 --> 00:02:48,579
♪ Even a lifetime of war
cannot be extinguished ♪

12
00:02:49,610 --> 00:02:50,740
♪ Blame me ♪

13
00:02:51,390 --> 00:02:54,890
♪ For the frailty of fate ♪

14
00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:57,560
♪ Hide me ♪

15
00:02:58,079 --> 00:03:02,090
♪ With light snow or thick ink ♪

16
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:05,900
♪ We met in the crowd ♪

17
00:03:06,690 --> 00:03:09,290
♪ There's no mistake in this life ♪

18
00:03:10,210 --> 00:03:13,200
♪ I only regret being clumsy in words ♪

19
00:03:13,220 --> 00:03:15,390
♪ And shrinking from speaking it out ♪

20
00:03:15,770 --> 00:03:18,230
♪ Even when destiny mocked me, hurt me ♪

21
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:20,040
♪ Destroyed me, or trapped me ♪

22
00:03:20,070 --> 00:03:22,540
♪ I never yielded ♪

23
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:24,340
♪ But why ♪

24
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:29,130
♪ Can't I bear to see
even a single tear in your eyes? ♪

25
00:03:29,530 --> 00:03:31,900
♪ But we once fell in love, went wild ♪

26
00:03:31,940 --> 00:03:33,790
♪ Split up, and lost each other ♪

27
00:03:33,820 --> 00:03:36,200
♪ They are
all unforgettable memories to me ♪

28
00:03:36,560 --> 00:03:38,320
♪ The first time I met you ♪

29
00:03:38,310 --> 00:03:39,440
Now,

30
00:03:38,690 --> 00:03:47,630
♪ It felt like something suddenly
lit up my soul ♪

31
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,930
I really won't make it back.

32
00:04:01,620 --> 00:04:02,730
♪ Blame me ♪

33
00:04:03,350 --> 00:04:06,850
♪ For the frailty of fate ♪

34
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,840
I know you want to protect me,

35
00:04:07,570 --> 00:04:08,800
but I don't want to be protected by you—

36
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:09,560
♪ Hide me ♪

37
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,030
because

38
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:14,050
♪ With light snow or thick ink ♪

39
00:04:10,650 --> 00:04:11,910
I want to stand with you

40
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,320
and fight by your side.

41
00:04:15,370 --> 00:04:17,790
♪ We met in the crowd ♪

42
00:04:16,829 --> 00:04:18,700
We're in the same boat to begin with.

43
00:04:18,649 --> 00:04:21,269
♪ There's no mistake in this life ♪

44
00:04:18,750 --> 00:04:21,950
I'll stand by you
and help you through this to the very end.

45
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:25,160
♪ I only regret being clumsy in words ♪

46
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:27,300
♪ And shrinking from speaking it out ♪

47
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,170
♪ Even when destiny mocked me, hurt me ♪

48
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:31,980
♪ Destroyed me, or trapped me ♪

49
00:04:32,010 --> 00:04:34,530
♪ I never yielded ♪

50
00:04:34,840 --> 00:04:36,360
♪ But why ♪

51
00:04:36,570 --> 00:04:41,110
♪ Can't I bear to see
even a single tear in your eyes? ♪

52
00:04:41,470 --> 00:04:43,830
♪ But we once fell in love, went wild ♪

53
00:04:43,880 --> 00:04:45,730
♪ Split up, and lost each other ♪

54
00:04:45,760 --> 00:04:48,090
♪ They are
all unforgettable memories to me ♪

55
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,260
♪ The first time I met you ♪

56
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:53,780
♪ There was once light ♪

57
00:04:54,390 --> 00:05:02,740
♪ In my soul ♪

58
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:11,330
♪ Even when destiny mocked me, hurt me ♪

59
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:13,140
♪ Destroyed me, or trapped me ♪

60
00:05:11,460 --> 00:05:12,920
Watch out, Your Highness!

61
00:05:13,170 --> 00:05:15,640
♪ I never yielded ♪

62
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,720
Wanyin...

63
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,520
♪ But why ♪

64
00:05:17,730 --> 00:05:22,300
♪ Can't I bear to see
even a single tear in your eyes? ♪

65
00:05:22,630 --> 00:05:24,990
♪ But we once fell in love, went wild ♪

66
00:05:25,040 --> 00:05:26,890
♪ Split up, and lost each other ♪

67
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,240
♪ They are
all unforgettable memories to me ♪

68
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:31,420
♪ The first time I met you ♪

69
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:39,880
♪ It felt like something suddenly
lit up my soul ♪

70
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,740
Your Highness, watch out!

71
00:05:46,890 --> 00:05:47,800
Xiahou Dan,

72
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:49,700
wait for me.

73
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,290
You're here.

74
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:34,930
♪ In the time and space of chaos ♪

75
00:06:35,740 --> 00:06:38,760
♪ Every time I open my eyes ♪

76
00:06:38,870 --> 00:06:39,480
I'm here.

77
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:42,670
♪ Your silhouette is engraved inside ♪

78
00:06:45,850 --> 00:06:48,590
♪ Then we transform ♪

79
00:06:49,230 --> 00:06:52,290
♪ Into the blazing light to guard ♪

80
00:06:52,659 --> 00:06:53,640
You're hurt.

81
00:06:52,670 --> 00:06:57,300
♪ Our eternal galaxy ♪

82
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:56,990
It's nothing.

83
00:06:58,170 --> 00:07:00,670
♪ Watch the universe bow ♪

84
00:06:58,170 --> 00:06:59,090
Just a minor injury.

85
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:04,020
♪ And let time freeze ♪

86
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,850
Let's stop the bleeding first.

87
00:07:04,720 --> 00:07:10,450
♪ I still gaze into those firm eyes ♪

88
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,080
♪ It doesn't matter ♪

89
00:07:12,750 --> 00:07:15,610
♪ The world set a trap with the stars
and the moon blocking the way ♪

90
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:17,790
♪ I'll still stand by your side ♪

91
00:07:17,820 --> 00:07:23,840
♪ Stand like an unbreakable wall
in troubled times ♪

92
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,040
Don't worry.

93
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,790
♪ Go to the battlefield ♪

94
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:29,170
♪ Waters surge in reverse,
and time rewinds ♪

95
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:27,750
I'm not going to die.

96
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,780
♪ Sever the mundane shackles ♪

97
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,470
I haven't helped you
fulfill your wish yet.

98
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,409
♪ We can dance together ♪

99
00:07:33,430 --> 00:07:41,290
♪ On the ruins fearlessly ♪

100
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,740
♪ It doesn't matter ♪

101
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:56,100
♪ The world set a trap with the stars
and the moon blocking the way ♪

102
00:07:56,790 --> 00:07:58,300
♪ I'll still stand by your side ♪

103
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:04,290
♪ Stand like an unbreakable wall
in troubled times ♪

104
00:08:02,830 --> 00:08:03,950
You bastard!

105
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:05,240
You monster!

106
00:08:04,930 --> 00:08:06,540
♪ Go to the battlefield ♪

107
00:08:05,700 --> 00:08:06,430
Get in there!

108
00:08:06,830 --> 00:08:09,790
♪ Waters surge in reverse,
and time rewinds ♪

109
00:08:07,190 --> 00:08:07,670
Kneel!

110
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:09,680
Dan.

111
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:12,330
♪ Sever the mundane shackles ♪

112
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:13,940
♪ We can dance together ♪

113
00:08:13,970 --> 00:08:21,830
♪ On the ruins fearlessly ♪

114
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:21,440
You Great Xia people are truly shameless.

115
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:23,140
What trash!

116
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,160
If it weren't for the fact that
Dan wants you alive,

117
00:08:27,160 --> 00:08:28,680
I'd have killed you long ago.

118
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,070
Do you think you'd still be here
cursing at us?

119
00:08:30,070 --> 00:08:30,900
Kill me then!

120
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,000
Kill me!

121
00:08:33,630 --> 00:08:34,120
Shut up!

122
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:35,659
Dan.

123
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,390
Hayuanwang.

124
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:37,320
Are you alright?

125
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:40,669
I'm okay, Mr. Bei.

126
00:08:40,669 --> 00:08:41,309
Haqina.

127
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:42,320
Haqina!

128
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,200
Haqina.

129
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,620
Hang in there, Haqina!

130
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,670
Prince Tu'er.

131
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:50,820
I... I stabbed him.

132
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:52,000
Haqina.

133
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:54,630
I'll kill you all!

134
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:56,160
I'll kill you all!

135
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,140
I'll kill you all!

136
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:02,200
Dan.

137
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:03,890
You want me to kill him?

138
00:09:06,670 --> 00:09:07,200
Mr. Bei,

139
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,120
don't.

140
00:09:10,390 --> 00:09:10,960
Kill him!

141
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:12,420
Why keep him alive?

142
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:15,740
So he can work with Prince Duan
from the outside?

143
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:17,120
I almost forgot

144
00:09:18,550 --> 00:09:19,950
that you're still alive.

145
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:25,720
You little brat.

146
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:40,910
If Prince Duan finds out that
the Yan's assassins failed,

147
00:09:40,910 --> 00:09:42,160
he'll go all the way

148
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,520
and carry out the regicide himself,

149
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:46,630
and he'll surely pin the blame on

150
00:09:46,630 --> 00:09:47,490
the Yan people.

151
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,910
His men are already lying in ambush
in the woods.

152
00:09:50,810 --> 00:09:54,340
[Be Remembered with Honor for All Ages]

153
00:09:52,970 --> 00:09:54,480
If we confront them head-on right now,

154
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:56,030
since we're badly outnumbered,

155
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:58,430
I don't have absolute confidence we'd win.

156
00:09:58,910 --> 00:10:01,320
Yang Duojie has gone to
mobilize the Imperial Guards.

157
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,450
The Imperial Guards

158
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:04,900
might not be so easy to be mobilized.

159
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:06,440
I trust him.

160
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:13,420
Then let's

161
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:16,330
just wait.

162
00:10:16,930 --> 00:10:18,990
Don't waste your energy, Xiahou Dan!

163
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:22,060
We smeared the Qiang State's poison
on our weapons.

164
00:10:22,120 --> 00:10:23,790
Your wound won't heal.

165
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,080
Your blood

166
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,720
will keep flowing

167
00:10:26,910 --> 00:10:27,700
and flowing,

168
00:10:28,270 --> 00:10:29,630
until it runs dry!

169
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:37,560
Someone.

170
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:38,440
Someone.

171
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:40,470
Someone!

172
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:43,100
Who are you?

173
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:44,360
Quick.

174
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,080
I need to see Commander Zhao.

175
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,540
Take me to Commander Zhao.

176
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,480
You think you can see Commander Zhao
just because you want to?

177
00:10:50,480 --> 00:10:52,120
Send the Imperial Guards up Mount Bei.

178
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,120
There's no time!

179
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:54,370
Don't try to fool me.

180
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:56,240
Commander Zhao?
What right do you have to see him?

181
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:57,370
That's impossible!

182
00:10:57,390 --> 00:10:57,720
I really...

183
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:59,450
Who's making a commotion here?

184
00:11:00,840 --> 00:11:01,770
Commander Zhao.

185
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,030
Commander Zhao!

186
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:07,600
Quick—lead the Imperial Guards
up Mount Bei to save His Majesty!

187
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:08,130
Quick...

188
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:10,340
Don't touch me.

189
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,410
Who are you?

190
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:19,600
I'm Yang Duojie, Director of
the Imperial Observatory.

191
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:23,510
-Quick, save His Majesty! There's no time!
-You said you're an Imperial Astronomer?

192
00:11:23,510 --> 00:11:24,770
What proof do you have?

193
00:11:25,960 --> 00:11:26,820
I have my badge.

194
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,120
My badge... My...

195
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:34,670
I just fled for my life from Mount Bei.

196
00:11:34,670 --> 00:11:36,290
I must have lost it on the way.

197
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,670
I wouldn't lie about
something this serious!

198
00:11:38,670 --> 00:11:40,360
I stake my life on it—

199
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,000
every word...

200
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,480
What use is your life to me?

201
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:44,650
Look at the state of you,

202
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:47,630
and you dare claim to be
from the Imperial Observatory

203
00:11:47,630 --> 00:11:50,160
and even try to mobilize
the Imperial Guards?

204
00:11:50,240 --> 00:11:50,840
Seize him!

205
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:53,260
I really...

206
00:11:53,570 --> 00:11:53,870
I...

207
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,550
-I'm really an Imperial Astronomer!
-Move!

208
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:58,160
Save His Majesty!

209
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,130
Commander Zhao!

210
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:02,800
Lock him up

211
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,750
and interrogate him strictly.

212
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:05,680
Yes, Commander.

213
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:19,070
Looks like the winds of power

214
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:21,140
are really about to shift.

215
00:12:25,200 --> 00:12:25,790
I take my leave.

216
00:12:25,790 --> 00:12:26,360
I take my leave.

217
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,360
Please take care.

218
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,120
Lord Jia.

219
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:33,480
Lord Jia.

220
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:36,670
Let's

221
00:12:37,320 --> 00:12:39,300
raise a cup to Lord Mu from afar

222
00:12:39,720 --> 00:12:41,360
for this brilliant plan.

223
00:12:44,390 --> 00:12:47,030
Lord Mu was using that name
for the sake of staying undercover.

224
00:12:47,030 --> 00:12:49,220
From now on, we should use his real name

225
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:50,390
and address him as

226
00:12:50,390 --> 00:12:52,100
Lord Murong.

227
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,390
Everyone knows the saying,

228
00:12:56,390 --> 00:12:58,790
"the mantis stalks the cicada,
unaware of the oriole behind."

229
00:12:58,790 --> 00:12:59,850
Little do they know

230
00:12:59,870 --> 00:13:02,870
His Highness Prince Duan's
"bird-catcher" strategy

231
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,050
is the truly brilliant one.

232
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:09,260
The time has not yet come,
and the outcome hasn't been decided yet.

233
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:12,550
Gentlemen, you should still
speak and act with caution.

234
00:13:12,550 --> 00:13:13,120
Yes.

235
00:13:19,480 --> 00:13:20,990
Stop wasting your energy.

236
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:23,970
[Be Remembered with Honor for All Ages]

237
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,790
I don't have the antidote.

238
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:24,790
Xiahou Dan.

239
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:28,250
I want you to savor the taste of death—

240
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:31,880
just as that foolish envoy you sent did!

241
00:13:33,670 --> 00:13:34,680
Look at me.

242
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:37,850
Do you really think he's still alive?

243
00:13:39,040 --> 00:13:39,780
Wang Zhao?

244
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:40,970
He...

245
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:42,450
He was killed.

246
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,360
Of course he was killed!

247
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,860
The entire real envoy delegation

248
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,390
has been killed by me!

249
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:54,730
Therefore,

250
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:56,360
ending the war and establishing trade

251
00:13:55,430 --> 00:13:59,060
[One month ago]

252
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:58,620
is not only a chance for the people
of both states

253
00:13:58,620 --> 00:14:00,700
to rest and recover,

254
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:03,360
but for you, Emperor,

255
00:14:03,630 --> 00:14:05,480
it can also help strengthen state power

256
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:07,010
and consolidate your rule—

257
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,510
a win on multiple fronts.

258
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,170
Good.

259
00:14:14,750 --> 00:14:15,200
Good.

260
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:16,720
Wonderful.

261
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:19,660
Excellent!

262
00:14:20,750 --> 00:14:23,020
I'm willing to send an envoy delegation

263
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:26,010
to return to Great Xia with you
for peace talks.

264
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,750
May our two states restore our friendship

265
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:29,790
-Good.
-and enjoy everlasting trade.

266
00:14:29,790 --> 00:14:30,850
Good. This is good.

267
00:14:33,360 --> 00:14:34,490
This cannot be done!

268
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:37,080
What are you doing here?

269
00:14:38,030 --> 00:14:38,800
Uncle.

270
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,480
Have you forgotten

271
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:42,940
the countless blood debts

272
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,120
the Xia people owe our Great Yan citizens?

273
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:46,860
Did Shanyi

274
00:14:47,270 --> 00:14:48,330
die for nothing?

275
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:49,390
Nonsense!

276
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:53,150
Peace talks are beneficial to
the Yan State.

277
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:56,310
Prince, you should learn to
look further ahead.

278
00:14:56,840 --> 00:14:59,170
Don't let personal grudges and old hatred

279
00:14:59,510 --> 00:15:00,640
blind you.

280
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:02,480
I'm speaking to my uncle.

281
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,760
There's no place for a Qiang woman
to speak.

282
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,200
Uncle.

283
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:10,840
Could it be that you're afraid of
the Xia people?

284
00:15:10,840 --> 00:15:11,840
If you are afraid,

285
00:15:13,030 --> 00:15:14,830
I, Tu'er, am not afraid of death.

286
00:15:15,270 --> 00:15:17,000
I'll lead our Great Yan warriors,

287
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,730
storm the Great Xia's capital,

288
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,410
and take
the Great Xia Emperor's head!

289
00:15:20,410 --> 00:15:20,910
Shut up!

290
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:22,660
Guards!

291
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:26,910
Take the Prince back to his tent
to reflect on his actions.

292
00:15:26,910 --> 00:15:28,840
Do not let him out without my order!

293
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:29,320
Yes!

294
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:34,520
Just you wait,

295
00:15:35,430 --> 00:15:36,830
you treacherous Xia dog.

296
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:43,670
Your Highness.

297
00:15:43,670 --> 00:15:44,510
Your Highness.

298
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:45,030
Your Highness.

299
00:15:45,030 --> 00:15:45,890
Your Highness.

300
00:15:46,390 --> 00:15:46,900
Now,

301
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:49,360
the peace talks have been announced
to the whole country.

302
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,510
The envoy delegation
sent by the Emperor of Yan

303
00:15:50,510 --> 00:15:52,570
has already set off for the Great Xia.

304
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:54,300
Your Highness.

305
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,600
What should we do?

306
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:06,960
Who among you is willing

307
00:16:07,510 --> 00:16:09,640
to follow me to the Great Xia's capital

308
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:12,130
and chop off their Emperor's head—

309
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,040
to make the Xia people

310
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:16,370
pay with their blood?

311
00:16:22,150 --> 00:16:24,570
We swear to follow Prince Tu'er
to the death!

312
00:16:24,570 --> 00:16:27,650
We swear to follow Prince Tu'er
to the death!

313
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:29,000
Kill!

314
00:16:29,390 --> 00:16:30,450
Protect Lord Wang!

315
00:17:02,270 --> 00:17:03,130
Run, Lord Wang!

316
00:18:10,350 --> 00:18:11,830
I will do my utmost

317
00:18:12,260 --> 00:18:13,960
to stop the war and establish trade.

318
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:14,760
I won't return

319
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:17,160
until I succeed.

320
00:18:25,340 --> 00:18:27,930
♪ In the time and space of chaos ♪

321
00:18:28,030 --> 00:18:28,550
You...

322
00:18:28,770 --> 00:18:31,810
♪ Every time I open my eyes ♪

323
00:18:32,500 --> 00:18:35,750
♪ Your silhouette is engraved inside ♪

324
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,620
♪ Then we transform ♪

325
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:45,350
♪ Into the blazing light to guard ♪

326
00:18:45,740 --> 00:18:50,390
♪ Our eternal galaxy ♪

327
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:49,040
[Be Remembered with Honor for All Ages]

328
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:53,650
♪ Watch the universe bow ♪

329
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:57,000
♪ And let time freeze ♪

330
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,100
Haqina!

331
00:18:57,400 --> 00:18:58,660
Haqina!

332
00:18:57,700 --> 00:19:03,450
♪ I still gaze into those firm eyes ♪

333
00:19:03,870 --> 00:19:05,100
♪ It doesn't matter ♪

334
00:19:05,780 --> 00:19:08,580
♪ The world set a trap with the stars
and the moon blocking the way ♪

335
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:10,810
♪ I'll still stand by your side ♪

336
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:16,820
♪ Stand like an unbreakable wall
in troubled times ♪

337
00:19:17,310 --> 00:19:18,740
♪ Go to the battlefield ♪

338
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,810
You'll surely face retribution!

339
00:19:19,290 --> 00:19:22,150
♪ Waters surge in reverse,
and time rewinds ♪

340
00:19:22,670 --> 00:19:24,810
♪ Sever the mundane shackles ♪

341
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:23,490
Stop moving!

342
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:24,480
Stop moving.

343
00:19:24,910 --> 00:19:26,440
♪ We can dance together ♪

344
00:19:26,460 --> 00:19:36,020
♪ On the ruins fearlessly ♪

345
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:30,400
You can't afford to lose any more blood.

346
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,750
I'm going to kill you all.

347
00:19:35,070 --> 00:19:36,470
I'm going to kill you all!

348
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:37,440
Kill you all!

349
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:46,400
Wang Zhao's mission was a secret.

350
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:52,350
Even his widowed mother
didn't know the truth.

351
00:19:54,930 --> 00:19:55,830
I told him

352
00:19:57,010 --> 00:19:58,800
that the journey would be perilous,

353
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:01,260
♪ Watch the universe bow ♪

354
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:01,930
and that he could refuse

355
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:04,620
♪ And let time freeze ♪

356
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:04,930
if he wished.

357
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:11,040
♪ I still gaze into those firm eyes ♪

358
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,480
But he said...

359
00:20:09,960 --> 00:20:11,510
I was born on the border
between the two states.

360
00:20:11,510 --> 00:20:12,590
♪ It doesn't matter ♪

361
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:13,680
Since childhood,

362
00:20:13,290 --> 00:20:16,150
♪ The world set a trap with the stars
and the moon blocking the way ♪

363
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:16,990
I've seen too many families
torn apart by war.

364
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:18,340
♪ I'll still stand by your side ♪

365
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,350
Most of my playmates

366
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:24,310
♪ Stand like an unbreakable wall
in troubled times ♪

367
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,370
also grew up like me,

368
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,040
unable to have

369
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,400
both parents alive.

370
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:26,240
♪ Go to the battlefield ♪

371
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,000
Some died

372
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:29,730
♪ Waters surge in reverse,
and time rewinds ♪

373
00:20:28,590 --> 00:20:29,590
before even

374
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:32,380
♪ Sever the mundane shackles ♪

375
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:31,680
reaching adulthood.

376
00:20:32,400 --> 00:20:34,040
♪ We can dance together ♪

377
00:20:33,820 --> 00:20:35,220
Their tiny bodies

378
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:41,780
♪ On the ruins fearlessly ♪

379
00:20:37,890 --> 00:20:40,090
could be wrapped in just half a reed mat.

380
00:20:44,680 --> 00:20:45,480
Your Majesty,

381
00:20:46,260 --> 00:20:48,260
peace talks are vital for our state.

382
00:20:48,590 --> 00:20:50,850
I'm willing to go with the resolve to die.

383
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:53,240
♪ It doesn't matter ♪

384
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,840
If anything should happen to me,

385
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:56,700
♪ The world set a trap with the stars
and the moon blocking the way ♪

386
00:20:54,860 --> 00:20:57,320
please build a cenotaph for me,
Your Majesty,

387
00:20:57,320 --> 00:20:58,890
♪ I'll still stand by your side ♪

388
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,050
so that my spirit

389
00:20:58,910 --> 00:21:04,890
♪ Stand like an unbreakable wall
in troubled times ♪

390
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:00,570
may return home.

391
00:21:02,270 --> 00:21:03,470
Then this life of mine

392
00:21:04,310 --> 00:21:05,590
will not have been lived in vain.

393
00:21:05,590 --> 00:21:07,140
♪ Go to the battlefield ♪

394
00:21:07,470 --> 00:21:10,410
♪ Waters surge in reverse,
and time rewinds ♪

395
00:21:10,820 --> 00:21:12,930
♪ Sever the mundane shackles ♪

396
00:21:12,950 --> 00:21:14,590
♪ We can dance together ♪

397
00:21:13,830 --> 00:21:16,230
I must ensure
his death was not for nothing,

398
00:21:14,630 --> 00:21:22,390
♪ On the ruins fearlessly ♪

399
00:21:18,430 --> 00:21:20,830
so that his spirit in heaven
may find peace.

400
00:21:25,390 --> 00:21:31,370
♪ Never looking back ♪

401
00:21:29,480 --> 00:21:30,350
Now,

402
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:33,940
let's proceed with

403
00:21:37,270 --> 00:21:38,200
the peace talks.

404
00:21:46,440 --> 00:21:48,240
What nonsense are you talking about?

405
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:48,720
Wanyin,

406
00:21:51,320 --> 00:21:52,620
give the gun to Mr. Bei

407
00:21:53,510 --> 00:21:55,590
and ask him to guard the gate properly.

408
00:21:55,590 --> 00:21:55,960
Okay.

409
00:22:04,590 --> 00:22:05,320
Buddy.

410
00:22:05,590 --> 00:22:06,790
What's your surname?

411
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:09,990
Buddy,

412
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:11,410
look at this.

413
00:22:12,250 --> 00:22:12,780
Look.

414
00:22:17,350 --> 00:22:18,440
Trying to bribe me

415
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:20,240
with just a few copper coins?

416
00:22:30,750 --> 00:22:32,410
With faith one may alter fate…

417
00:22:33,550 --> 00:22:34,680
Marvelous.

418
00:22:37,910 --> 00:22:39,510
No, no, not marvelous at all!

419
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:44,720
What're you talking about,
marvelous or not?

420
00:22:44,720 --> 00:22:45,680
Just now,

421
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,660
I cast a hexagram for you
using the Six Lines.

422
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:53,050
There's a great calamity in your fate!

423
00:22:54,750 --> 00:22:56,480
If you keep spouting nonsense,

424
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:58,940
I'll use the torture instruments on you.

425
00:22:59,510 --> 00:23:02,190
I'm the Director of
the Imperial Observatory,

426
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:06,350
in charge of divining fortune
and misfortune for the royal destiny.

427
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:07,070
Whether you believe my reading

428
00:23:07,070 --> 00:23:07,730
is up to you,

429
00:23:09,270 --> 00:23:11,780
and whether you can keep your new position

430
00:23:12,200 --> 00:23:13,510
as Deputy Commander

431
00:23:14,350 --> 00:23:15,400
is also up to you.

432
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:17,720
How do you know

433
00:23:18,310 --> 00:23:20,160
I was just promoted to Deputy Commander?

434
00:23:20,160 --> 00:23:21,290
The will of Heaven

435
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:23,530
cannot be revealed.

436
00:23:26,400 --> 00:23:28,280
Buddy, I wonder if you've heard

437
00:23:28,680 --> 00:23:29,780
the story of Cao Cao

438
00:23:30,110 --> 00:23:31,720
and Wang Hou?

439
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:33,480
What Wang Hou?

440
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:34,010
Wait,

441
00:23:34,240 --> 00:23:35,480
what does this have to do with me?

442
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:38,400
My dear buddy,
it has everything to do with you!

443
00:23:41,790 --> 00:23:43,290
It is said that when Cao Cao

444
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:44,640
went to conquer Yuan Shu,

445
00:23:44,640 --> 00:23:47,640
he encountered a drought,
and the army ran out of food.

446
00:23:47,720 --> 00:23:50,120
The grain officer, Wang Hou,
asked Cao Cao,

447
00:23:51,920 --> 00:23:53,790
"without food to eat,

448
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,600
what should we do?"

449
00:23:58,510 --> 00:23:59,100
"Replace

450
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:00,550
the large bushel with a smaller one

451
00:24:00,550 --> 00:24:03,130
when issuing the rations to them."

452
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,690
"But the soldiers will be resentful.

453
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:06,790
What then?"

454
00:24:06,790 --> 00:24:07,450
"No matter.

455
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:10,850
I have a brilliant plan."

456
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:12,480
Once the rations were reduced,

457
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,650
the soldiers were indeed furious.

458
00:24:15,030 --> 00:24:16,020
And then, Cao Cao

459
00:24:16,400 --> 00:24:17,860
said to the grain officer,

460
00:24:19,790 --> 00:24:22,200
"I need to borrow one more thing from you

461
00:24:22,270 --> 00:24:24,030
to steady the army's morale."

462
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:25,760
"What is it?"

463
00:24:26,030 --> 00:24:26,680
"Your

464
00:24:27,110 --> 00:24:29,240
head."

465
00:24:30,350 --> 00:24:32,910
"I am innocent! Truly innocent!"

466
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,400
"I know you are innocent.

467
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:35,250
But

468
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,700
if I don't execute you,

469
00:24:36,920 --> 00:24:39,790
should I execute myself?"

470
00:24:47,240 --> 00:24:48,310
W-What are you talking about?

471
00:24:48,310 --> 00:24:49,710
Beating around the bush.

472
00:24:51,790 --> 00:24:52,790
Buddy,

473
00:24:53,070 --> 00:24:54,200
aren't you just like

474
00:24:54,730 --> 00:24:56,810
that Wang Hou right now?

475
00:24:59,720 --> 00:25:00,160
Look,

476
00:25:00,650 --> 00:25:03,450
Zhao Wucheng could have just
asked you to watch me.

477
00:25:03,480 --> 00:25:05,310
Why did he have to
order you to interrogate me

478
00:25:05,310 --> 00:25:06,830
in front of everyone?

479
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:13,990
For failing to save His Majesty,

480
00:25:13,990 --> 00:25:15,570
someone's head has to roll.

481
00:25:17,590 --> 00:25:19,650
Even if His Majesty were to pass away,

482
00:25:19,710 --> 00:25:21,170
Prince Duan would still
pursue this charge

483
00:25:21,170 --> 00:25:22,700
to make a show of his stance.

484
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:25,550
That Zhao Wucheng is Prince Duan's lackey,

485
00:25:25,550 --> 00:25:27,010
so of course he'll be fine.

486
00:25:27,510 --> 00:25:29,160
Then the one who'll be in trouble

487
00:25:29,160 --> 00:25:31,570
can only be whoever fails to get results
from the interrogation

488
00:25:31,570 --> 00:25:33,630
and delays the deployment of troops.

489
00:25:38,590 --> 00:25:39,850
Did you divine all this

490
00:25:40,880 --> 00:25:42,290
from your hexagrams?

491
00:25:44,630 --> 00:25:51,340
[Be Remembered with Honor for All Ages]

492
00:25:45,100 --> 00:25:46,640
You're a dying man,

493
00:25:47,110 --> 00:25:48,420
and I'm a desperado.

494
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:50,550
What's there for us to talk about?

495
00:25:50,550 --> 00:25:52,010
Don't even think about it!

496
00:25:52,750 --> 00:25:53,440
Indeed.

497
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:55,520
Just take it as

498
00:25:56,750 --> 00:25:58,110
the ramblings

499
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:01,070
of a dying man.

500
00:26:02,240 --> 00:26:03,300
Bring him forward.

501
00:26:03,650 --> 00:26:08,530
[Be Remembered with Honor for All Ages]

502
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,210
Years of war

503
00:26:14,590 --> 00:26:16,390
have left the people destitute.

504
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,510
You didn't notice,

505
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,940
but Zhaluowahan realized

506
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:24,320
that the people
have lost the will to fight.

507
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:27,160
He needs time

508
00:26:27,960 --> 00:26:29,030
to recuperate,

509
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,610
and he also needs a new opportunity

510
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:36,480
to stir up

511
00:26:37,310 --> 00:26:39,040
the people's fighting spirit.

512
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,840
The Xia people know they are in the wrong,

513
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:43,690
[When two states go to war,
one is bound to suffer.]

514
00:26:43,030 --> 00:26:45,440
so they sent someone with a peace treaty.

515
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,440
[Prolonged war is no blessing to a state.
I seek terms with the Yan State.]

516
00:26:44,460 --> 00:26:45,080
[Let's set aside old grievances,
forge an alliance, and keep the peace.]

517
00:26:45,110 --> 00:26:45,690
[I hereby draft this pact
as a pledge of good faith and trust.]

518
00:26:46,030 --> 00:26:48,100
The court ministers and the people

519
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:50,330
really don't want any more war.

520
00:26:50,550 --> 00:26:52,790
I don't want to go against
their wishes either.

521
00:26:52,790 --> 00:26:53,850
But Shanyi...

522
00:26:55,480 --> 00:26:58,480
She was our holy maiden!

523
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,480
Shanyi was just a young girl.

524
00:27:04,590 --> 00:27:07,590
Why would she attempt an assassination
for no reason?

525
00:27:08,030 --> 00:27:08,920
Who was it

526
00:27:10,260 --> 00:27:11,590
that gave her the order?

527
00:27:12,920 --> 00:27:14,120
And how did the person

528
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:17,280
who gave the order make her obey?

529
00:27:18,830 --> 00:27:20,030
Coercion or bribery?

530
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:23,240
Or did they use her beloved

531
00:27:24,070 --> 00:27:25,030
to threaten her?

532
00:27:33,640 --> 00:27:34,640
How did Xiahou Dan

533
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,090
know all this?

534
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:41,770
Being a puppet without even realizing it—

535
00:27:43,670 --> 00:27:45,400
you can't save the one you love,

536
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,920
nor can you find your true enemy.

537
00:27:51,070 --> 00:27:53,130
Do you really think the Emperor of Yan

538
00:27:53,580 --> 00:27:56,000
has no idea that you've come to
the Great Xia?

539
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,320
Just like Shanyi,

540
00:27:58,590 --> 00:28:00,850
your deaths in the palace of the Great Xia

541
00:28:01,440 --> 00:28:04,240
would be far more useful
than dying at their hands.

542
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,480
When the news reaches the Yan State,

543
00:28:07,880 --> 00:28:09,740
he can shed crocodile tears again

544
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:11,270
and cry

545
00:28:13,110 --> 00:28:15,050
for the Xia State to pay in blood.

546
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,240
You're right.

547
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,130
I... I am a puppet.

548
00:28:27,330 --> 00:28:28,390
But what about you?

549
00:28:28,830 --> 00:28:29,960
Aren't you one, too?

550
00:28:30,350 --> 00:28:31,590
Of course I am.

551
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:36,720
When I was young, I thought

552
00:28:37,570 --> 00:28:39,700
that if I fought with everything I had,

553
00:28:40,190 --> 00:28:41,960
I could escape their control.

554
00:28:43,400 --> 00:28:45,130
But later, I slowly realized

555
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,100
that every decision I made

556
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:50,140
and my every act of resistance

557
00:28:51,790 --> 00:28:53,520
played right into their hands.

558
00:28:56,750 --> 00:28:58,440
I am a puppet,

559
00:29:00,270 --> 00:29:01,510
a target,

560
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,240
and an arrow.

561
00:29:14,590 --> 00:29:17,440
I am the killing blade in their hands,

562
00:29:23,750 --> 00:29:25,480
yet the one thing I cannot be

563
00:29:29,550 --> 00:29:30,210
is a person.

564
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,140
Is what he's talking about

565
00:29:35,350 --> 00:29:38,350
the experience of Xiahou Dan
from the original story?

566
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:42,110
Actually, we are very much alike.

567
00:29:44,110 --> 00:29:45,310
But I'm not resigned—

568
00:29:49,350 --> 00:29:51,590
I refuse to pretend to be ignorant,

569
00:29:52,720 --> 00:29:55,110
to drift blindly toward fate,

570
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:57,570
or to deceive myself

571
00:29:58,240 --> 00:29:59,200
and call it

572
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:02,660
"having no choice."

573
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,160
Are you resigned?

574
00:30:09,350 --> 00:30:10,590
Are you?

575
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:17,690
Kneel!

576
00:30:26,030 --> 00:30:28,440
You actually lost your composure
over a woman,

577
00:30:28,440 --> 00:30:30,100
ignoring the bigger picture!

578
00:30:30,640 --> 00:30:33,010
How can I entrust the Great Yan to you?

579
00:30:33,680 --> 00:30:35,340
How can you ever be an emperor?

580
00:30:35,590 --> 00:30:37,790
If I can't even protect the woman I love,

581
00:30:38,590 --> 00:30:41,310
then I'm not fit
to be the Emperor of the Yan State!

582
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:42,040
You bastard!

583
00:30:45,790 --> 00:30:46,250
Guards!

584
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,740
Yes, Your Majesty!

585
00:30:48,110 --> 00:30:49,040
Pass on my order:

586
00:30:49,550 --> 00:30:51,350
say that the Prince has gone mad.

587
00:30:51,720 --> 00:30:52,850
From this day forth,

588
00:30:53,550 --> 00:30:55,220
he is not to leave the camp.

589
00:30:55,720 --> 00:30:57,380
If he still refuses to repent,

590
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,400
starve him!

591
00:30:58,720 --> 00:30:59,780
Yes, Your Majesty.

592
00:31:07,480 --> 00:31:08,660
I never expected

593
00:31:08,830 --> 00:31:11,030
that you'd be such a hopeless romantic.

594
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,180
Since that's the case,

595
00:31:15,030 --> 00:31:16,290
I'll give you a poison.

596
00:31:17,790 --> 00:31:19,480
Smear it on a wound,

597
00:31:21,350 --> 00:31:23,480
and the blood will drain, ending life.

598
00:31:26,920 --> 00:31:28,480
Go find your Shanyi.

599
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:51,070
Hate me if you want.

600
00:31:51,590 --> 00:31:52,880
I'm a dying man,

601
00:31:54,030 --> 00:31:55,360
and you're a desperado.

602
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:59,000
It's just the one
who truly killed your beloved

603
00:32:01,310 --> 00:32:03,640
can continue to sit securely on the throne

604
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,520
with nothing to worry about.

605
00:32:11,270 --> 00:32:12,200
Unfortunately,

606
00:32:13,890 --> 00:32:15,200
I'm about to die.

607
00:32:17,160 --> 00:32:20,360
If you could kill
that treacherous Emperor Zhaluowahan,

608
00:32:21,480 --> 00:32:23,010
it would be good news for me,

609
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:25,930
and you would get your revenge.

610
00:32:26,640 --> 00:32:27,310
But now,

611
00:32:29,350 --> 00:32:31,060
you've committed regicide.

612
00:32:33,030 --> 00:32:35,160
You probably don't even stand a chance

613
00:32:36,670 --> 00:32:38,400
of leaving the Great Xia alive.

614
00:32:57,240 --> 00:32:59,100
I really don't have the antidote.

615
00:33:00,110 --> 00:33:02,170
That Qiang woman only gave me poison.

616
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:05,580
Go find your imperial physicians

617
00:33:06,350 --> 00:33:08,150
and try to figure something out.

618
00:33:16,160 --> 00:33:18,370
Then please pray hard for me.

619
00:33:22,600 --> 00:33:24,600
Then tell me how to turn this around.

620
00:33:26,790 --> 00:33:27,350
Speak!

621
00:33:27,920 --> 00:33:31,120
To think there're people
so disrespectful of propriety—

622
00:33:31,830 --> 00:33:34,490
you ask for guidance
yet won't even bow to learn.

623
00:33:35,030 --> 00:33:36,830
I can be even more disrespectful.

624
00:33:36,830 --> 00:33:38,430
Are you going to speak or not?

625
00:33:41,620 --> 00:33:42,070
Buddy.

626
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,690
Can you get the Tiger Tally?

627
00:33:51,030 --> 00:33:52,360
Greetings, Commander.

628
00:33:53,400 --> 00:33:54,790
How's the interrogation going?

629
00:33:54,790 --> 00:33:55,310
Commander,

630
00:33:55,310 --> 00:33:56,160
I haven't got anything out of him yet.

631
00:33:56,160 --> 00:33:59,090
I'll definitely
conduct a thorough interrogation.

632
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,380
Interrogate him properly

633
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:21,000
and meticulously.

634
00:34:22,510 --> 00:34:24,770
This is an important matter of the state.

635
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:28,710
Both you and I will be credited for this.

636
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:31,070
Yes, sure.

637
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:37,330
Please take care, Commander.

638
00:34:57,360 --> 00:34:58,090
No survivor.

639
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:00,260
Let's go

640
00:35:00,510 --> 00:35:01,440
and kill them all.

641
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:01,760
Yes.

642
00:35:07,590 --> 00:35:09,450
I really don't have the antidote.

643
00:35:10,800 --> 00:35:11,190
Dan!

644
00:35:13,670 --> 00:35:15,070
Those ambushed in the woods

645
00:35:15,070 --> 00:35:15,930
have closed in.

646
00:35:18,500 --> 00:35:18,830
Run.

647
00:35:19,550 --> 00:35:20,080
Let's go.

648
00:35:20,190 --> 00:35:20,630
I...

649
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,610
I don't think I can run anymore.

650
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,200
Then let's find a place

651
00:35:38,480 --> 00:35:39,000
to hide

652
00:35:39,400 --> 00:35:39,920
and wait.

653
00:35:39,920 --> 00:35:40,720
Wait for what?

654
00:35:41,760 --> 00:35:42,810
A chance—

655
00:35:44,110 --> 00:35:45,310
to see whether Heaven

656
00:35:45,690 --> 00:35:47,340
stands on our side.

657
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,230
Let's get in the underground palace.

658
00:35:53,230 --> 00:35:53,760
Let's go.

659
00:36:03,030 --> 00:36:04,030
What are you doing?

660
00:36:04,030 --> 00:36:04,720
Let go of me!

661
00:36:28,400 --> 00:36:29,640
I will lure them away

662
00:36:29,800 --> 00:36:31,610
to buy Your Majesty some time.

663
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:47,380
Wanyin.

664
00:36:55,070 --> 00:36:56,470
This underground palace

665
00:36:56,510 --> 00:36:58,070
is like a shelter.

666
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:01,970
Its locking stone falls into a groove,

667
00:37:03,630 --> 00:37:05,370
forming a triangle

668
00:37:05,710 --> 00:37:07,480
with the stone gate and the ground.

669
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:08,810
Without special tools,

670
00:37:09,480 --> 00:37:11,410
it's hard to open with brute force.

671
00:37:11,920 --> 00:37:12,710
This is

672
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:15,960
the stability of a triangle.

673
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:18,360
Not bad, CEO Dan.

674
00:37:18,800 --> 00:37:20,000
You still remember what you learned

675
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:21,260
back in middle school.

676
00:37:22,280 --> 00:37:23,230
After all, it is

677
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:26,100
the crystallization of ancient wisdom.

678
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:46,830
Lord Cao.

679
00:37:47,110 --> 00:37:48,960
We didn't find the bodies of
His Majesty and Tu'er.

680
00:37:48,960 --> 00:37:50,590
Keep searching. They won't get far.

681
00:37:50,590 --> 00:37:50,970
Yes.

682
00:37:51,710 --> 00:37:52,240
Found it!

683
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:52,810
Found it!

684
00:37:53,550 --> 00:37:54,760
There is blood
near the underground palace.

685
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:55,760
They must be hiding there.

686
00:37:55,760 --> 00:37:57,370
What are you waiting for? Go!

687
00:38:11,270 --> 00:38:11,940
My Lord.

688
00:38:12,110 --> 00:38:12,850
The gate is blocked from inside.

689
00:38:12,850 --> 00:38:14,380
His Majesty must be inside.

690
00:38:17,510 --> 00:38:18,640
Break the gate down.

691
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:45,550
Harder!

692
00:38:47,510 --> 00:38:48,910
Bring the battering ram!

693
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:50,550
Yes!
